author: kameshj
msg: Fix the bug introduced in r27494, the bug is 'multiple begin merge
notifications i.e for every operative merge on any node results in
a merge-beging notification.'
* subversion/libsvn_client/merge.c
(notification_receiver): Notify 'merge-begin' notification only once.

author: kfogel
msg: Follow up to r27424 with documentation and parameter tweaks.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/commit.c
(get_version_url): Give this function a doc string.
Also, move its return parameter to the front, as per modern
Subversion coding conventions.  All callers changed.
Also, change a parameter from 'name' to 'relpath', because it will
be used in a call to a 'svn_ra_get_wc_prop_func_t' function, and
the 'name' parameter to that function means something different
(the code was correct, but the name 'name' was confusing).
